<%= render "layouts/navbar" %>
<section id="hero">
    <h2 class="section-heading">Welcome to A&W</h2>
    <h2 class="section-heading">Our Mission</h2>
    <div>
        <p>
            A&W Canada's mission is to make A&W the #1 burger choice for Baby Boomers and the fastest-growing, most successful burger business in Canada.

            Their vision focuses on quality, sustainability, and community:

            Serve high-quality food like hormone- and antibiotic-free beef and natural root beer.
            Lead in environmental responsibility with compostable packaging and waste reduction.
            Support communities through initiatives like "Burgers to Beat MS," raising over $20 million for Canadians with Multiple Sclerosis.
        </p>
        <div class="full-menu-button">
            <%= link_to "View Full Menu", products_path, class: "button is-warning" %>
        </div>
</section>
<section class="section featured-products">
    <div class="container">
        <h2 class="title is-2 has-text-centered mb-6 ">Featured Items</h2>

        <div class="columns is-multiline">
            <% @featured_products.each do |product| %>
            <div class="column is-one-quarter full-card">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-image">
                        <figure class="image is-4by3">
                            <% if product.image.attached? %>
                            <%= image_tag product.image, alt: product.name %>
                            <% else %>
                            <div class="no-image">
                                <span class="has-text-grey">No Image</span>
                            </div>
                            <% end %>
                        </figure>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p class="title is-5"><%= product.name %></p>
                        <p class="subtitle is-6">
                            <span class="tag is-primary"><%= product.category %></span>
                        </p>
                        <p class="has-text-weight-bold has-text-primary">
                            $<%= number_with_precision(product.price, precision: 2) %>
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <footer class="card-footer">
                        <%= link_to "View Details", product_path(product), class: "card-footer-item" %>
                    </footer>
                </div>
            </div>
            <% end %>
        </div>

        <div class="has-text-centered mt-5 full-button-menu">
            <%= link_to "View Full Menu â†’", products_path, class: "button is-primary" %>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
<section>
    <section id="faq" class="">
        <h2 class="section-heading">FAQ</h2>
        <!-- FAQ content -->
        <div class="faq-div">
            <p>Q: What makes A&W different from other fast-food chains?</p>
            <p>A: A&W focuses on quality and sustainability from hormone and steroid free beef to compostable packaging and community-driven campaigns like Burgers to Beat MS.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-div">
            <p>Q: Does A&W use real ingredients?</p>
            <p>A: Yes! Our tomatoes are grown in energy-efficient greenhouses, allowing them to ripen naturally on the vine. We also source fair-trade organic coffee and avoid artificial growth hormones in our beef.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-div">
            <p>Q: Why does A&W care so much about the environment?</p>
            <p>A: We listen to our guests and franchisees who value sustainability. From reusable dine-in ware to eliminating plastic straws, we aim to lead the industry in reducing environmental impact.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-div">
            <p>Q: How does A&W support Canadian communities?</p>
            <p>A: Through long-standing partnerships like Burgers to Beat MS, we raise funds and awareness for important causes, with franchisees actively involved in local initiatives.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-div">
            <p>Q: Is A&W packaging recyclable or compostable?</p>
            <p>A: Almost all of our packaging is compostable. Dine-in customers enjoy meals on real ceramic plates with metal cutlery, further reducing waste.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
</section>